      "writtenOn": "2021-04-30T13:45:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Without this, the PathEdgeIter doesn\u0027t report the first contour as a new contour, so the path clipper would insert a spurious moveTo(0,0) while building the clipped path. During rendering of filled clipped-paths, that extra line is degenerate and doesn\u0027t show up, but it does change the bounds reported by path.getBounds().\n\nI ran into it while trying to use path.getBounds() as the ground truth for mapRect. @reed, does this fix seem reasonable to you since you wrote the edge iter and path clipping?",
